NAME
----
xe-pif-param-add - Add a key/value to a parameter for a physical interface (PIF)

SYNOPSIS
--------
*xe pif-param-add* uuid=<PIF UUID> param-name=<PARAMETER> [ <MAP PARAMETER KEY>=<VALUE> ] [ param-key=<SET PARAMETER KEY> ] 

DESCRIPTION
-----------
*xe pif-param-add* adds a key/value pair to a map parameter or a key to a set parameter. Use *xe pif-list* and *xe pif-param-list* to identify writable set or map parameters (SRW, MRW).ï»¿

REQUIRED PARAMETERS
-------------------
*uuid*::
	PIF UUID - Use *xe pif-list* to obtain a list of PIF UUIDs.
*param-name*::
	Parameter to have key or key/value pair added - Use *xe pif-param-list* to obtain a list of PIF parameters.

OPTIONAL PARAMETERS
-------------------
*param-key*::
	Key to be added to a set parameter (SRW)
*<MAP PARAMETER KEY>*::
	Key/value pair to be added to a map parameter (MRW)

EXAMPLES
--------
To add the key/value pair "management_purpose=Storage" to the map parameter *other-config*: 

- *xe pif-param-add* uuid=<PIF UUID> param-name=other-config management_purpose=Storage

